comments.body:
The PR removes the dependency instead which also works.

I was suggesting this to try and reproduce it, however, you are right, this seems like it's a more complicated race:
{noformat}
cmake ../cpp -GNinja -DARROW_FLIGHT=ON -DARROW_PLASMA=ON -DARROW_DEPENDENCY_SOURCE=BUNDLED
ninja src/plasma/CMakeFiles/plasma_objlib.dir/plasma.cc.o {noformat}
This does show that there's no dependency edge to Abseil (since no prerequisites get built), but I guess the issue is Flatbuffers searching for string_view + the headers being in the middle of installation when this happens.
